    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-head">Before You Go</div>
      <div class="outro">
        <p>The Wendigo is hunger. Slenderman is dread. The Black-Eyed Children are something harder to name — patient, present everywhere there is a threshold, knocking politely and asking reasonably and waiting.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:18px;">Brian Bethel is still alive, thirty years after a night in an Abilene parking lot, because he listened to his body before he listened to his conscience. Because he was willing to be the person who did not help two children who needed a ride. Because the locked door of his car was the only protection he had — and he kept it locked.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:18px;">You have the same protection. Whatever you live in, whatever you sail in, whatever you drive — the boundary is real. <em>The threshold holds.</em> Only as long as you let it.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:18px;">This has been the Monster Survival Guide. Stay inside. Stay sceptical. And if something knocks tonight — do not answer it to find out what it is.</p>
